data.name: CharaDataHub.GposeTogether.Help
data.value:
GPose together is a way to do multiplayer GPose sessions and collaborations.
GPose together requires Brio to function. Only Brio is also supported for the actual posing interactions. Attempting to pose using other tools will lead to conflicts and exploding characters.
To use GPose together you either create or join a GPose Together Lobby. After you and other people have joined, make sure that everyone is on the same map. It is not required for you to be on the same server, DC or instance. Users that are on the same map will be drawn as moving purple wisps in the overworld, so you can easily find each other.
Once you are close to each other you can initiate GPose. You must either assign or spawn characters for each of the lobby users. Their own poses and positions to their character will be automatically applied. Pose and location data during GPose are updated approximately every few seconds.

data.name: CharaDataHub.Mcd.Online.Help
data.value:
In this tab you can create, view and edit your own Character Data that is stored on the server.
Character Data Online functions similar to the previous MCDF standard for exporting your character, except that you do not have to send a file to the other person but solely a code.
There would be a bit too much to explain here on what you can do here in its entirety, however, all elements in this tab have help texts attached what they are used for. Please review them carefully.
Be mindful that when you share your Character Data with other people there is a chance that, with the help of unsanctioned 3rd party plugins, your appearance could be stolen irreversibly, just like when using MCDF.

data.name: DataAnalysis.Bc7.WarningDetails
data.value: - Converting textures to BC7 will reduce their size (compressed and uncompressed) drastically. It is recommended to be used for large (4k+) textures. - Some textures, especially ones utilizing colorsets, might not be suited for BC7 conversion and might produce visual artifacts. - Before converting textures, make sure to have the original files of the mod you are converting so you can reimport it in case of issues. - Conversion will convert all found texture duplicates (entries with more than 1 file path) automatically. - Converting textures to BC7 is a very expensive operation and, depending on the amount of textures to convert, will take a while to complete.

data.name: CharaDataHub.NearbyPoses.Help
data.value:
This tab will show you all Shared World Poses nearby you.
Shared World Poses are poses in character data that have world data attached to them and are set to shared. This means that all data that is in 'Shared with You' that has a pose with world data attached to it will be shown here if you are nearby. By default all poses that are shared will be shown. Poses taken in housing areas will by default only be shown on the correct world and location.
Shared World Poses will appear in the world as floating wisps, as well as in the list below. You can mouse over a Shared World Pose in the list for it to get highlighted in the world.
You can apply Shared World Poses to yourself or spawn the associated character to pose with them.
You can adjust the filter and change further settings in the 'Settings & Filter' foldout.
